content:
Bitcoin mining firm Iris Energy <a href="https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/01/12/2587795/0/en/Iris-Energy-Announces-Monthly-Investor-Update-for-December-2022.html" data-v-f87c67ca="">reported</a> that its operating revenue declined 27% in December compared to the previous month to $2.1 million — reflecting the first full month of operations after terminating some hosting arrangements.&nbsp;<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The firm mined 19% less bitcoin in December, with its average operation hashrate falling 25% to 1,086 PH/s. Operating capacity increased 30% over the period to 1.5 EH/s in that time.&nbsp;
